 and then obtain connections from it, same as above:

    Connection conn = dataSource.getConnection();
    Statement stmt = conn.createStatement();
    ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery(&quot;SELECT ID FROM USERS&quot;);
    
    rs.close();
    stmt.close();
    conn.close();

In modern Java, use [try-with-resources][4] syntax to automatically close JDBC resources (now [`AutoCloseable`][5]).

